cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.DS

This paper deals with the theoretical properties of bagging, a popular technique used in machine learning, to improve the generalization performance of unstable algorithms. As such, it is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses the performance of statistical estimators, which suggests a possible classification under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm to estimate the variance of a sample, which could potentially fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
